annotation.TEXT: Argh! I can't believe I let the top of my hat get nicked by that evil star!
Whoa! That Sumo Dooder tried to ambush me! Once again, quick reflexes FTW!
Hmm... Yeah, I think a spare feather would be more useful here.
More current fighting here, just like before.
The game wants me to "R" again. Fine, I'll do it.
Aw... This area only got an "A", not an "A+" like the main area did. But, an "A" is still really good.
Now, I'm probably going to play them both next time, but which one should I play first? That'll be up to the voters to decide!
Goal tape average so far: 3462 / 88 = 39.341 stars each.
Whoop! Gotta spin jump here.
So, place your votes for either 8-4 or 8-C, and we'll find out which order I play those levels next time! To be continued...
I nearly nicked my hat again, but I avoided it this time!
That's a tricky star coin that requires a mole bounce to get safely.
Umm... Doesn't look like it, and perhaps jumping down here wasn't a good idea. But, I think I can maybe get back up with a max speed jump...
Oh, nice! Another cape! Let's try not to lose this one, okay?
Whoa, man! I really wish I had a cape right now!
Alright, a power up. It's only a mushroom, but I'll take anything right now.
Whoa! Now I've gotta be careful of everything here!
Thwack! Nice.
Ugh! And, even knowing he was there, I still got hammered!
Better do this part right, or I might end up with unreachable coins.

So, I'm guessing that after raocow found that glitch and got sent to the bonus game trap, Kona put actual exits on each screen of these evil star levels, which just send the player back to start, or to the midpoint entrance instead if the player was on or past the screen that the midpoint's on.
Whoops. Well, whatever. I think the goal is just up ahead anyway, so the shell would've only been worth another feather. Speaking of the goal, let's hope I can time this right...
Hmm... Well, I guess a flower would be potentially useful against the moles here.
Here's some more Pokey bouncing.
Umm... What do I have to... Oh, I gotta make a running jump and bounce off of some fragile blocks.
Oh, man. There's currents that I've gotta deal with. However, the horizontal current isn't terribly strong, so I just have to fight it carefully.
Careful, the currents you're fighting start changing direction on you here. (Also, you might've noticed that the evil stars above the first such current change looked like an exclamation point.)
Okay, now remember where I showed you those note blocks earlier... Yeah. If you didn't remember that, this is a blind jump.
Hmm... That Sumo Duder isn't on hittable blocks, and he's guarded from the left by an evil star. Killing him will be tricky.
Sure, I'll take the fire flower.
Wish granted! Sweet!

Ah, nice. It would've been very easy to come in at the wrong time and get stuck with a horrible star score there, but I got a 40, which is good. (It would be nice if I could get some 50s to make up for last episode's goal tape hits, though.)
Ha! The sprite limit made one of his lightning bolts fail to appear. Oh, maybe if I bounce off of a mole, I might be able to attack the Sumo Guy from the right...
Okay, now I know there's a Hammer Duder right near the start here...
I want all of the coins!

Now, truth be told, after I was done with 8-2 before, I did some experimenting off screen with the evil star pipe entrance glitch, and no matter where I did it, it reset the level. However, if I was around midpoint or later, it sent me to midpoint instead of the beginning of the level, so I figured it would be the same here.
More nicking my hat on an evil star, just like before...
Hmm... Call me crazy, but I'm going to try something that's probably a very bad idea. And yes, it involves the extra power up and taking an intentional hit.
Awesome! This gets rid of two columns of evil stars. Now, let me just fix the camera and then see if I can grab that shell again...
Now, I just want to see what's to the left that the side area skipped over, like usual.
Whoa, well that Pokey kinda just fell. He was probably placed like that to let players know that they've gotta bounce off of that Pokey below.
And that opens up a level that wants to milk me to death in its own way. Wait, that sounded wrong.
I wonder why the glitch with the evil star hurt blocks even exists in the first place, though...
Oh, I just got an idea. Let's see if I can use a certain glitch to my advantage here...
GAAAMMMEEE!!!

Note: As for that tie-breaker idea up there, I considered it, but I was only going to do that if it would potentially make a difference. Since 8-B won by so much here, there was no need for me to bother with such a tie-breaker.
I'm actually a little surprised that the Klingon language doesn't seem to have words for "ludicrous", "speed", or "bonus". Seriously, not even the common word "speed"?
Make sure to hit all three of these timed lifts in quick succession, because you do need them all!
"R" you say... What if I want to "L" instead?
BGM: Phoenix Wright - Cornered
And, that appears to be it for this bonus room.
Bonk! I like how the Sumo Duders so far have been on hittable blocks.
Plenty of moles and evil stars, and there's the turn block pillar that led to the side area.
'ej toH, ludicrous speed bonus Quj.
So, there are two levels available for me to pick from again, 8-4 Death Milky Way, and 8-C Skewering Fortress.
While I'm at it, is there anything else of interest up here?
Bonk!
Oh, there is so something up above these turn blocks.
Gotta dodge this guy now, since I can't kill him this time (not that I'd want to try that again).

And then I nick that unfortunate corner of my shoe again on my way out. Sure, why not? Well, it only took me about half a minute to go from having a surplus power up available to no power ups at all...
Okay, see where those note blocks are on the right? Remember that for later, viewers.
Mmm... Lie... (*drools*)
Oh, I remember this spot from raocow's video. The path you take determines which prize you get. Ah, but I can "cheat" a little bit with the "R" button.
Hello, and welcome back to Super Marina World! Let's see which level I'll be going to next...
Alright, 8-B won, so let's mosey on up there...
Made it! Now I can clobber that Sumo Brother!

Found a hidden note block, but why am I wasting time with this secret? Well, for one thing, the last star coin is up here, which lets me know I'm near the end of the level, and if I didn't get it now, I'd be repeating the level to look for it!
Zwee!
Ah, and if I remember right, this block contains a shell, which I've gotta use to reveal a pair of vines over there.
Whoa! Ha! Gotcha! Quick reflexes FTW!

Now, despite these currents being light-colored, they're strong enough to support me even if I'm not holding a jump button here. (Which is probably a good thing in case the player doesn't have a cape.)
Here goes...

I'll take that flower right there. I forget what's further below (perhaps there's a cape), but I just want a guaranteed power up right now. (Oh, and no, you cannot run against these currents. They're way too powerful.)
And that unlocks 8-C, which I guess is a fortress that loves to skewer things. Now, 8-3 came in second in the voting (which was kind of assured), so let's head there next!
Goal tape average so far: 3502 / 89 = 39.348 stars each.
Hey, Marina. You did it wrong! You were supposed to bounce off of those fragile blocks, not skip them completely! Anyway, there are some moles to deal with around here.
And here we've got some timed lifts, and some jumps that we've gotta carefully time.
Yes, my plan worked perfectly, and I now have a cape! However, this also cost me a decent amount of time, so I've gotta hustle now!
Um, yeah. I'm just going to float over this whole mess.
Yep, there's a pipe. And... Let me just do a bit of screen scrolling to make sure there's nothing else nearby...

Seriously, there had to be a single "helpful" hidden block right there? Oy. However, this means that Kona must've expected someone to try getting up here like I just did, and put that block there so they could get out more easily.
Ha! Just as I thought! It shrunk me and sent me back to midpoint, but since this reset the level, I can get the next two power ups again!
Okay, there's a power up I don't need, and a Sumo Guy over there that seems completely blocked off.
Oh, man. Is this where I'm going to find the fourth evil star piece of the Evil Star Road?
Oh, nice! This level earned an "A+"! Oh, wait, there's an "X" as well? Well, screw that! I'll use "Y" instead!
Bonus game average so far: 246 / 34 = 7.235 1♥Ps each.
Time to do some celestial exercise!
Whew! I'm glad I had enough time to reach the goal, after all the time-wasting I did earlier!
Well, I can "L", but that didn't reveal much of interest, so I guess I'd better "R" like it says.
Okay, now I wish for a million dollars! ...What do you mean I only get one wish and I just used it?
Thank you, cape! I guess this wish isn't so bad... Still, a million dollars would've been nice...
